article.headline: Robert Morris 78, Wagner 74
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Velton Jones scored a career-high 29 points to lead Robert Morris past Wagner 78-74 on Thursday night in the Northeast Conference quarterfinals. The Colonials (17-13) led 69-57 with less than 4 minutes remaining, but the Seahawks went on a 13-3 run to pull within two, 72-70, with 25 seconds to go. Robert Morris went 6 of 6 from the free-throw line over the final 23 seconds to seal the win. Coron Williams had 16 points and Lijah Thompson added 13 for the Colonials, who led 38-21 at halftime after shooting 50 percent from the floor (12 of 24), including 6 of 7 from 3-point range (85.7 percent) in the opening half. Tyler Murray scored 19 points, Orlando Parker added 16 and Chris Martin and Latif Rivers each had 14 for Wagner (13-17). No. 3 Robert Morris will face No. 2 Quinnipiac (22-8) in the semifinals -- a rematch of the 2010 NEC tournament championship game.
